<subSubSection id="C35EC39F8416FF88FF57FD9EFE1DD364" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BFB90148416FF88FF57FD9EFE1DD364" blockId="5.[151,1437,152,1738]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FF57FD9EFEEDD2FF" bold="true" box="[198,343,631,657]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">Etymology:</emphasis>
This species is named in honor of Dr. Osmar Domaneschi, a Brazilian malacologist, for his contribution to the knowledge of functional anatomy of the pelecypods and his contribution to the SBMa (Sociedade Brasileira de Malacologia, Brazilian Malacological Society) for which he served more than 10 years as vice president.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35EC39F8416FF88FF57FCFEFDACD6A4" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFB90148416FF88FF57FCFEFD1CD3EC" blockId="5.[151,1437,152,1738]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FF57FCFEFEFBD35F" bold="true" box="[198,321,791,817]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">Remarks:</emphasis>
Because of the similarities among the genera of 
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FC1AFCF1FC4AD35C" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[907,1008,792,818]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Limidae</taxonomicName>
, we chose to compare our proposed new taxon with all the species that are characterized mainly by the presence of concentric ornamentation, regardless of their present generic allocation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFB90148416FF88FF54FC79FE42D424" blockId="5.[151,1437,152,1738]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FF54FC79FE57D3C4" authority="Allen, 2004" authorityName="Allen" authorityYear="2004" box="[197,493,912,938]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lirata">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FF54FC79FEE2D3C7" box="[197,344,912,937]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">Limea lirata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD5EDE58416FF88FEF3FC79FE57D3C4" author="Allen, J. A." box="[354,493,912,938]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" pagination="2591 - 2653" refId="ref7048" refString="Allen, J. A. (2004) The Recent species of the genera Limatula and Limea (Bivalvia, Limacea) present in the Atlantic, with particular reference to those in deep water. Journal of Natural History, 38, 2591 - 2653." type="journal article" year="2004">Allen, 2004</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is more oblique and somewhat more rounded than 
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FBC4FC79FAB3D3C7" authority="Oliveira &amp; Absalão, 2008" authorityName="Oliveira &amp; Absalão" authorityYear="2008" box="[1109,1289,912,937]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="domaneschii" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FBC4FC79FAB3D3C7" box="[1109,1289,912,937]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">L. domaneschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A203F17D8416FF88FA82FC79FAF0D3C4" box="[1299,1354,912,938]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Moreover, 
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FF4AFC51FE84D3BF" authorityName="Allen" authorityYear="2004" box="[219,318,952,977]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lirata">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FF4AFC51FE84D3BF" box="[219,318,952,977]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">L. lirata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is ornamented with numerous concentric lines, which are closer to each other and cover the entire shell; the umbones are more slender and comparatively more projected beyond the hinge than the umbones of 
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FEBEFBE1FE5CD44F" authority="Oliveira &amp; Absalão, 2008" authorityName="Oliveira &amp; Absalão" authorityYear="2008" box="[303,486,1032,1057]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="domaneschii" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FEBEFBE1FE5CD44F" box="[303,486,1032,1057]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">L. domaneschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A203F17D8416FF88FE61FBE1FD92D44C" box="[496,552,1032,1058]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The main difference is the very fine axial ridges in 
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FB3EFBE1FAA9D44F" authorityName="Allen" authorityYear="2004" box="[1199,1299,1032,1057]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lirata">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FB3EFBE1FAA9D44F" box="[1199,1299,1032,1057]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">L. lirata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which are absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FE96FBD9FE00D427" authority="Oliveira &amp; Absalão, 2008" authorityName="Oliveira &amp; Absalão" authorityYear="2008" box="[263,442,1072,1097]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="domaneschii" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FE96FBD9FE00D427" box="[263,442,1072,1097]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">L. domaneschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A203F17D8416FF88FE50FBD9FE42D424" box="[449,504,1072,1098]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFB90148416FF88FF54FBB1FDCDD5E4" blockId="5.[151,1437,152,1738]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FF54FBB1FE71D41F" authority="Oliveira &amp; Absalão, 2008" authorityName="Oliveira &amp; Absalão" authorityYear="2008" box="[197,459,1112,1137]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="domaneschii" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FF54FBB1FE71D41F" box="[197,459,1112,1137]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">Limatula domaneschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A203F17D8416FF88FE43FBB1FDB3D41C" box="[466,521,1112,1138]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FCD8FBB1FB36D41C" authority="(Smith, 1885)" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[841,1164,1112,1138]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="laminifera">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FCD8FBB1FC58D41F" box="[841,994,1112,1137]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">L. laminifera</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD5EDE58416FF88FC63FBB1FB3ED41C" author="Smith, E. A." box="[1010,1156,1112,1138]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref7642" refString="Smith, E. A. (1885) Report on the Lamellibranchiata collected by H. M. S. Challenger during the years 1873 - 76. Challenger Reports, Zoology. 13, 1 - 341, 1 - 25 pls." type="book chapter" year="1885">Smith, 1885</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by the presence, in the latter, of an elongated, triangular ligamental pit, ornamentation over the entire shell, the presence of an auricular sinus, a slender umbo, and a short hinge plate; whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FCC2FB41FBBFD4AF" authority="Oliveira &amp; Absalão, 2008" authorityName="Oliveira &amp; Absalão" authorityYear="2008" box="[851,1029,1192,1217]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="domaneschii" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FCC2FB41FBBFD4AF" box="[851,1029,1192,1217]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">L. domaneschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A203F17D8416FF88FB9DFB41FBF9D4AC" box="[1036,1091,1192,1218]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has a rounded ligamental pit, the dorso-central region without ornamentation, no auricular sinus, and a comparatively large umbo and hinge plate. Also, 
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FEB9FB11FE79D57F" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[296,451,1272,1297]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="laminifera">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FEB9FB11FE79D57F" box="[296,451,1272,1297]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">L. laminifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bears, internally, two thickened axial ridges at the middle of the shell, and axially oriented slender striae, but both characters are absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FCD3FAC9FC4DD557" authority="Oliveira &amp; Absalão, 2008" authorityName="Oliveira &amp; Absalão" authorityYear="2008" box="[834,1015,1312,1337]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="domaneschii" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FCD3FAC9FC4DD557" box="[834,1015,1312,1337]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">L. domaneschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A203F17D8416FF88FB90FAC9FB83D554" box="[1025,1081,1312,1338]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Additionally, 
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FB77FAC9FA26D557" authority="Oliveira &amp; Absalão, 2008" authorityName="Oliveira &amp; Absalão" authorityYear="2008" box="[1254,1436,1312,1337]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="domaneschii" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FB77FAC9FA26D557" box="[1254,1436,1312,1337]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">L. domaneschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A203F17D8416FF88FF06FAA1FF74D50C" box="[151,206,1352,1378]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has the dorsal edge raising upwards slightly, which does not occur in any other species known from the Brazilian coast and the surrounding area.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFB90148416FF88FF54FA71FEFAD63C" blockId="5.[151,1437,152,1738]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FF54FA71FE20D5DF" authorityName="Clarke" authorityYear="1974" box="[197,410,1432,1457]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="louiseae">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FF54FA71FE20D5DF" box="[197,410,1432,1457]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">Limatula louiseae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FE4BFA71FD35D5DF" authority="Oliveira &amp; Absalão, 2008" authorityName="Oliveira &amp; Absalão" authorityYear="2008" box="[474,655,1432,1457]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="domaneschii" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FE4BFA71FD35D5DF" box="[474,655,1432,1457]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">L. domaneschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A203F17D8416FF88FD0BFA71FD6BD5DC" box="[666,721,1432,1458]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
share the concentric ornamentation, but the former species shows the diagnostic microscopic diagonal striae that are absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FC3FFA29FBD8D5B7" authorityName="Oliveira &amp; Absalão" authorityYear="2008" box="[942,1122,1472,1497]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="domaneschii">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FC3FFA29FBD8D5B7" box="[942,1122,1472,1497]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">L. domaneschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
n.sp.. Besides that, 
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FADCFA29FF69D66F" authorityName="Clarke" authorityYear="1974" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="louiseae">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FADCFA29FF69D66F" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">L. louiseae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is slender (height/length ratio 1.53), its prodissoconch is small (
<quantity id="4CBC3DF18416FF88FC2CFA01FBA9D66C" box="[957,1043,1511,1538]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.09" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" unit="mm" value="109.0">109µm</quantity>
) and the ligamental pit is triangular, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FEBAF9F9FE65D647" authorityName="Oliveira &amp; Absalão" authorityYear="2008" box="[299,479,1552,1577]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="domaneschii">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FEBAF9F9FE65D647" box="[299,479,1552,1577]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">L. domaneschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
n.sp, has a height/length ratio of 1.43, a prodissoconch of 
<quantity id="4CBC3DF18416FF88FB03F9F9FB57D644" box="[1170,1261,1551,1578]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" unit="mm" value="170.0">170 µm</quantity>
and a rounded ligamental pit.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFB90148416FF88FF54F989FDACD6A4" blockId="5.[151,1437,152,1738]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">
A comparison with the 87 
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FD93F989FDD6D617" authorityName="Wood" authorityYear="1839" box="[514,620,1632,1657]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FD93F989FDD6D617" box="[514,620,1632,1657]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">Limatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presumed species in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD5EDE58416FF88FCFBF989FBA6D614" author="Stuardo, J." box="[874,1052,1632,1658]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" refId="ref7765" refString="Stuardo, J. (1968) On the phylogeny, taxonomy and distribution of the Limidae (Mollusca: Bivalvia). PhD thesis, Harvard University, Cambridge, MA, USA, 327 pp." type="book" year="1968">Stuardo (1968)</bibRefCitation>
showed no close similarity with 
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FF06F961FEF0D6CF" authority="Oliveira &amp; Absalão, 2008" authorityName="Oliveira &amp; Absalão" authorityYear="2008" box="[151,330,1672,1697]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="domaneschii" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FF06F961FEF0D6CF" box="[151,330,1672,1697]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">L. domaneschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FEC3F96EFE37D6CF" bold="true" box="[338,397,1671,1697]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A203F17D8416FF88FEC3F96EFE37D6CF" box="[338,397,1671,1697]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
; most of them have dominant axial ornamentation while 
<taxonomicName id="4C44EB978416FF88FBA0F961FB5ED6CF" authorityName="Oliveira &amp; Absalão" authorityYear="2008" box="[1073,1252,1672,1697]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="domaneschii">
<emphasis id="B9304C068416FF88FBA0F961FB5ED6CF" box="[1073,1252,1672,1697]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">L. domaneschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
n.sp has exclusively concentric ornamentation.
</paragraph>
